ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.
M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: Scale describing ability to think clearly in the past 7 days as part of the Multidimensional Inventory of Subjective Cognitive Impairment (MISCI)
Notes: 1= Not at all; 2= A little bit; 3= Somewhat; 4= Quite a bit; 5= Very much

ElementDescription: Scale describing perception about extent of mental sharpness the past 7 days as part of the Multidimensional Inventory of Subjective Cognitive Impairment (MISCI)
Notes: 1= Not at all; 2= A little bit; 3= Somewhat; 4= Quite a bit; 5= Very much

ElementDescription: Scale describing ability to remember in the past 7 days as part of the Multidimensional Inventory of Subjective Cognitive Impairment (MISCI)
Notes: 1= Not at all; 2= A little bit; 3= Somewhat; 4= Quite a bit; 5= Very much

ElementDescription: Scale describing ability to learn new things in the past 7 days as part of the Multidimensional Inventory of Subjective Cognitive Impairment (MISCI)
Notes: 1= Not at all; 2= A little bit; 3= Somewhat; 4= Quite a bit; 5= Very much

ElementDescription: Scale describing ability to concentrate in the past 7 days as part of the Multidimensional Inventory of Subjective Cognitive Impairment (MISCI)
Notes: 1= Not at all; 2= A little bit; 3= Somewhat; 4= Quite a bit; 5= Very much

ElementDescription: Scale describing ability to pay attention in the past 7 days as part of the Multidimensional Inventory of Subjective Cognitive Impairment (MISCI)

ElementDescription: Scale describing trouble shifting back and forth between activities that require thinking in the past 7 days as part of the Multidimensional Inventory of Subjective Cognitive Impairment (MISCI)
Notes: 1= Never; 2= Rarely; 3= Sometimes; 4= Often; 5= Very often

ElementDescription: Scale describing trouble planning out steps of a task in the past 7 days as part of the Multidimensional Inventory of Subjective Cognitive Impairment (MISCI)

ElementDescription: Scale describing need to work harder than usual to express self clearly in the past 7 days as part of the Multidimensional Inventory of Subjective Cognitive Impairment (MISCI)

ElementDescription: Scale describing trouble finding the right word(s) to express self in the past 7 days as part of the Multidimensional Inventory of Subjective Cognitive Impairment (MISCI)
Notes: 1= Never; 2= Rarely; 3= Sometimes; 4= Often; 5= Very often

ElementDescription: Calculated total (raw) score for the Multidimensional Inventory of Subjective Cognitive Impairment (MISCI)
Calculated normalized t-score for the Multidimensional Inventory of Subjective Cognitive Impairment (MISCI)
